## Why Some Devices Stop Here

Samsung's update promise depends on when a device launched. Phones and tablets released in 2023 were sold under the **older 4-major-OS-upgrade policy** — the 7-year promise didn't start until the Galaxy S24 series in 2024. For these 2023 devices, **One UI 9 (Android 17) completes that four-upgrade cycle**, and there's no fifth update coming behind it.

That doesn't mean the device stops working. It means no more new features, no new Galaxy AI tools, and no version bump past Android 17. Security patches continue for roughly another year on a quarterly basis, then the device exits support entirely.

